subject: ethernet: Expose VLAN interfaces as EthernetInterface
commitMessage:
ethernet: Expose VLAN interfaces as EthernetInterface

In OpenBMC, VLAN is a virtual interface that has its own configuration
like IP address. Redfish schema also suggests using individual
EthernetInterface to show VLAN information. This patch exposes VLAN
interfaces as EthernetInterface for configuring them.

Now bmcweb also shows BMC VLAN interfaces under /​redfish/​v1/​Managers
/​bmc/​EthernetInterfaces.

Fixes bmcweb issue #79 (Unable configure IP on VLAN interface via
redfish).

Tested:
* Both physical and VLAN interfaces are now in the interface collection
* Only VLAN interfaces have the VLAN property, while only physical ones
  have VLANs pointing to the VLanNetworkInterfaceCollection
* IP address of both physical and VLAN interfaces can be modified by
  PATCH request successfully
* Redfish validator passed

Change-Id: Ic9a5fdc69388e14212b0cc55e5a585562ec8ca39
Signed-off-by: Jiaqing Zhao <jiaqing.zhao@intel.com>

Looks correct to me.

This does not appear to follow the Redfish schema.
These items should be populated below a VLANNetworkInterfaceCollection.

These changes don't appear to belong to parseInterfaceData, but belong to parseVlanInterfaceData.

The vlanId needs to be std::vector in order to correctly enumerate all of the possible VLAN entries that may exist.

Any LAN entry in parseInterfaceData is, by definition, Physical. Any collected from parseVLANInteraceData is Virtual.

It follows the schema. VLanNetworkInterface 1.3.0 says "This schema has been deprecated in favor of using individual EthernetInterface resources to show VLAN information." (Why I implement the new schema as long as keeping the deprecated 

The "EthernetDeviceType" property added in EthernetInterface v1.6 indicates the interface is a physical or vitural interface.

> "Virtual": "This value shall indicate a network device function has multiple VLANs and is representing one of them as a virtual Ethernet interface.  The NetworkDeviceFunction property within Links shall contain the locator for the parent network device function."

https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/EthernetInterface.v1_6_4.json

Missing something at the end of first paragraph, Why I implement the new schema as long as keeping the deprecated has mentioned in another comment.

Having vlan virtual interfaces exposed in EthernetInterface is to support configuring the virtual interfaces like IP address mentioned in https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/issues/79
Ack
Shall we separate this bump to a separate commit?
Moved the schema bump part to https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/54011
Ack
This change looks like it needs some additional work to make it compliant to the Redfish schema.

This is Redfish schema compliant, I had a discussion in Redfish forum at https://redfishforum.com/thread/619/proper-create-using-ethernetinterface-schema

Here I implements what I proposes in that theread, keep using the deprecated VLanNetworkInterface for creating/deleting VLANs, while also exposes the VLAN interfaces under /​redfish/​v1/​Managers/​bmc/​EthernetInterfaces/​ for configuring them. This workaround will be here until redfish spec reached a solution, after that, remove the VLANs property.
It's no wonder there's some confusion.
